# Plugin standards

**Naming:** Slug = lowercase hyphenated (e.g. `engineer-move-serials`). Use for: folder name, main file `<slug>.php`, text domain, script handles. Options/transients: `slug_with_underscores_*`. Constants/classes: UPPER_SNAKE / PascalCase from slug. Plugin header: **`(Chameleon) Plugin Name`**, Author, Author URI, Plugin URI (chameleoncodewing.co.uk).

**Deploy:** Installed path `wp-content/plugins/<slug>/`; main file `<slug>.php` in that folder. Zip: one top-level folder = slug; contents = plugin files. Store zips in **`dist/<slug>/`** (or `plugins/dist/<slug>/` in multi-plugin repos). Build script in `scripts/` (e.g. `build-zip.ps1`); run after any plugin change.

**Version:** MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH. **PATCH** on every change: update `VERSION` file, CHANGELOG entry, main file Version header in same commit. **MINOR** for new features; **MAJOR** for explicit new release. Never commit a version bump without a changelog entry.

**Zip retention:** Keep 5 most recent + all X.0.0 zips. Script `.\scripts\cleanup-plugin-zips.ps1`; run from project root. Build script should call cleanup after each build. See plugin-zip-retention.mdc for policy.
